{"TopicId":153107,"ForumId":148,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program 1.2.2 is live!","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-06T22:42:48Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:34:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878303\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481113863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294319\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ExtremeTrader\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, ExtremeTrader said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EPlease add a previous_1.2.1 beta version to steam, I don\u0027t want to wait for 65 plugins to be updated...\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s extremely likely that those plugins still work, just ignore the version warnings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s also good practice to backup your modded installs somewhere outside of Steam,\u00A0and turn off automatic updates for the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerospike","CreatedById":159274,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:38:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481114089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s extremely likely that those plugins still work, just ignore the version warnings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s also good practice to backup your modded installs somewhere outside of Steam,\u00A0and turn off automatic updates for the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can highly recommend both suggestions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481109799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250750\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Azimech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Azimech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity\u003C/strong\u003E, what about a voting system, which bugs should be solved first? Shall we open a new topic for this? Maybe it helps if Squad can give an estimate how much resources is needed for every problem, some are more difficult and costly than others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA voting system might actually free up some resources, Squad. It will probably reduce complaining from the community as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sounds like a good idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"asdfCYBER","CreatedById":94319,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:41:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481114089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s extremely likely that those plugins still work, just ignore the version warnings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s also good practice to backup your modded installs somewhere outside of Steam,\u00A0and turn off automatic updates for the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, just tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got a screen full of version warnings. After loading my save I was at the wrong planet, Kopernicus is version-locked. And due to that, various (adapted) mods were spamming NullReferenceExceptions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it can\u0027t be that hard to add a previous-version-beta, right? Squad has done it in the past (1.0.5, 1.1.2).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T12:42:50Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 12:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by ExtremeTrader\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:42:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed,\u00A0 I have 50\u002B versions of KSP on my HD, all running. Some versions have a specific set of mods, for a single purpose (for example mod development). I can revisit all my creations, it\u0027s great to have such a museum of my geekiness.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:45:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878035\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481085416\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SkyKaptn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, SkyKaptn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome. Just got my mods up to date with 1.2.1 Here we go again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481085491\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnever fails... and you know it will happen again in about 2 months... very frustrating and exhausting\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s why I don\u0027t update right away. \u00A0I was on 1.0.4 for the longest time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T12:54:26Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 12:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by klgraham1013\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T12:56:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481084630\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022171352\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rayden\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Rayden said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E* Fix where some science experiments only trigger once on action groups.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBesides the terrain seams, this was the only bug I was actually experiencing. \u00A0So 1 bug down, 1 more to go.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 It\u0027s progress... now to wait for some of my mods to get updated. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481090276\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, but they do cause rollovers and wheel damage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgain no, though it makes it 9000 times more aggravating. On Eve, hitting one will almost certainly break your tires. Anywhere else, it\u0027ll probably flip you over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRaised (specifically seams in the runway, but same bug) in the 1.2 prerelease, hence the irritation that it\u0027s still not fixed 2 patches later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Seeing as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0are both reading the thread, maybe they could address the terrain seams issue? \u00A0Is it being actively worked on? \u00A0Was it a more difficult problem than anticipated and will be in 1.2.3? \u00A0Is it not considered a major issue at all?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T12:57:51Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 12:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by klgraham1013\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T13:25:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481109799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250750\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Azimech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Azimech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity\u003C/strong\u003E, what about a voting system, which bugs should be solved first?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing the \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Ecan agree on these days is Squad isn\u0027t fixing that \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Emember\u0027s personal \u0022most important\u0022 bug. The only thing nobody in the \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Ecan agree on is which bug that is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a bug being annoying and a bug being fixable are different things. I\u0027d rather Squad fix 100 easily fixable bugs that I don\u0027t personally suffer from (but ohters do) than spend all their time on 3 bugs I care about (but nobody else does).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T13:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878355\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481117137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing the \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Ecan agree on these days is Squad isn\u0027t fixing that \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Emember\u0027s personal \u0022most important\u0022 bug. The only thing nobody in the \u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity \u003C/strong\u003Ecan agree on is which bug that is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a bug being annoying and a bug being fixable are different things. I\u0027d rather Squad fix 100 easily fixable bugs that I don\u0027t personally suffer from (but ohters do) than spend all their time on 3 bugs I care about (but nobody else does).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t it a bit premature for such an opinion? We\u0027ll only know for sure if/when we have a voting system. I wrote with a reason it\u0027s good to have an estimate how many resources a specific bug would need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T14:12:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878307\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481114475\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294319\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ExtremeTrader\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, ExtremeTrader said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, just tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got a screen full of version warnings. After loading my save I was at the wrong planet, Kopernicus is version-locked. And due to that, various (adapted) mods were spamming NullReferenceExceptions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it can\u0027t be that hard to add a previous-version-beta, right? Squad has done it in the past (1.0.5, 1.1.2).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the things I learned when watching Scott Manley\u0027s KSP vids is \u003Cstrong\u003Enever\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Einstall mods into your Steam KSP folder, keep that as a pristine untouched version. Make a copy of the KSP folder for a modded play.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KroShan","CreatedById":90357,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T14:55:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481114089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s extremely likely that those plugins still work, just ignore the version warnings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s also good practice to backup your modded installs somewhere outside of Steam,\u00A0and turn off automatic updates for the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027Turn off automatic updates in steam\u0027 is no longer possible. One can just choose to update on gamestart - but that doesn\u0027t help much. So only your first advice is applicable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T14:59:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878442\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481122538\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290357\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KroShan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, KroShan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027Turn off automatic updates in steam\u0027 is no longer possible. One can just choose to update on gamestart - but that doesn\u0027t help much. So only your first advice is applicable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQue? Just go to Steam/SteamApps/Common, copy the whole KSP folder to a spot you want on your harddrive and presto, you can now run the version from the new location and it will never be updated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:00:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878442\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481122538\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290357\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KroShan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, KroShan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027Turn off automatic updates in steam\u0027 is no longer possible. One can just choose to update on gamestart - but that doesn\u0027t help much. So only your first advice is applicable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate on game start is hugely useful, as it gives you the opportunity to back up your install before the update is applied (this is what I was referring to).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"asdfCYBER","CreatedById":94319,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:07:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878447\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481122804\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate on game start is hugely useful, as it gives you the opportunity to back up your install before the update is applied (this is what I was referring to).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know. I forgot to set the update policy to \u0027update on launch\u0027. But it would still be nice if \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E could add 1.2.1 to the list of beta\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: the other thing I could try to do is removing Kopernicus\u0027 version-lock, if I can find it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T15:10:18Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 03:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by ExtremeTrader\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KroShan","CreatedById":90357,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:10:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50750-azimech/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250750\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50750-azimech/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Azimech\u003C/a\u003E thats the first advice i was referring to...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/12858-red-iron-crown/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002212858\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/12858-red-iron-crown/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Red Iron Crown\u003C/a\u003E so the game foulder keeps untouched from the update \u0027till it is complete? Thats indeed useful. THX\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DevonKiwi","CreatedById":131965,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:12:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne change not mentioned (I think).\u00A0 Key binding for Kerbals\u0027 helmet lights changed from \u0027L\u0027 to \u0027U\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starwaster","CreatedById":71262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:17:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481109799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250750\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Azimech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Azimech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity\u003C/strong\u003E, what about a voting system, which bugs should be solved first? Shall we open a new topic for this? Maybe it helps if Squad can give an estimate how much resources is needed for every problem, some are more difficult and costly than others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA voting system might actually free up some resources, Squad. It will probably reduce complaining from the community as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is such a voting system already in place if you participate in the bug tracker.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:20:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878460\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481123860\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271262\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starwaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Starwaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is such a voting system already in place if you participate in the bug tracker.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I use it as well. I\u0027m not impressed with it. And I\u0027d like to have one on the forum, so we can discuss it and Squad can inform us what the cost would be to solve an issue, which in turn could influence our voting behaviour.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:27:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222877716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481065502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, we wait.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the download to complete.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd for all the mods to be updated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Terwin","CreatedById":139655,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T15:37:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222877681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481064168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UomoCapra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, UomoCapra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E* Fix to prevent kerbals with existing name being created.\n* Fix where some science experiments only trigger once on action groups.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought the experiments thing was due to a mod I had installed, glad to see it is fixed as that was quite vexing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood to see\u00A0duplicate kerbal names will no longer cause problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this for all places the names are generated, including manually entered names in the kerbal generator(cheat menu)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T15:37:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 03:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Terwin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"captainzeldaman","CreatedById":171872,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T16:24:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat Stuff! And my mods didn\u0027t break either!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rayden","CreatedById":171352,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T16:26:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222878323\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481115399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Seeing as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0are both reading the thread, maybe they could address the terrain seams issue? \u00A0Is it being actively worked on? \u00A0Was it a more difficult problem than anticipated and will be in 1.2.3? \u00A0Is it not considered a major issue at all?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps it\u0027s this \u0022terrain seams\u0022 bug is not on all platforms. \u00A0I see it in Linux (Ubuntu 14.04) 64-bit. \u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EI know\u003C/strong\u003E it\u0027s not a memory problem because I got 32 GB of RAM in my machine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rspeed","CreatedById":8514,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T16:46:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! This will make my science rover will be so much easier to use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, UomoCapra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E* Fix MPL(Science lab) ladder sliding.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Qwarkk","CreatedById":154770,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T16:51:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis update completely ruined my UI on all screens. Excellent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyRender","CreatedById":10651,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T16:59:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was really hoping that rovers would be fixed so they can actually be driven in any frame of reference again instead of only when your control point is facing the horizon.\u00A0 Not everyone drives rovers with a seat attached, you know!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T17:07:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222877681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481064168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UomoCapra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, UomoCapra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022 style=\u0022font-family:monospace, monospace;font-size:14px;background:rgb(250,250,250);clear:both;white-space:pre-wrap;padding:2px;border:1px solid rgb(136,136,136);color:rgb(39,42,52);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);\u0022\u003E* Fix null reference exception when overwriting SubAssemblies in \u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:1px dotted;\u0022 title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:1px dotted;\u0022 title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis update broke my workflow! My mouse doesn\u0027t reach the \u0022Launch\u0022 button, so I overwrite SubAssemblies\u00A0instead, and I configured the debug menu\u00A0to interpret a NRE as a Launch command.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}